source/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.928413551826301e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 250}, {\"ngram\": \"way\", \"from\": 267, \"to\": 270}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 278}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But what do we know about these, some of the world's most sought-after objects?\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 383, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world's most sought-after objects\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 382}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For a start, they could not be much more French.\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 433, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a start\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 396}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The medals' ribbons were specially woven in France, and the world's biggest luxury company LVMH designed the medals, which were cast in the Paris Mint.\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 478, \"end\": 484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999994633869013, \"rank\": 5.089179321050422e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The medals' ribbons\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 453}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's biggest luxury company\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 524}, {\"ngram\": \"LVMH\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 529}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 549}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Mint\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And - in a unique move - the Paris 2024 medals also feature pieces of the Eiffel Tower embedded in them.\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 615, \"end\": 625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9083052857288363e-